{"id": "41039", 
"title": "Hitting the Enter/Return key in the Find/Replace dialog doesn't trigger a 'Find' operation on Mac OS X", 
"description": "Hitting the Enter/Return key in the Find/Replace dialog doesn't do anything on Mac OS X.", 
"OB": "", 
"EB": "Eclipse 3.0 M2Build id: 200307181617, Mac OS X 10.2.6", 
"SR": "1) Open the Find/Replace dialog (Edit -> Find/Replace).\n2) Type a search term into the text box.\n3) Press the Enter/Return key.\nExpected Behavior: The Enter/Return key should trigger a 'Find' operation, similar to clicking on the 'Find' button, which is highlighted as the default button in the Find/Replace dialog."}
